How spark execute code???

SQL Query / DataFrame
        │
        ▼
1. Parsing
(Unresolved Logical Plan)
        │
        ▼
2. Analysis (Catalog Check)
(Resolved Logical Plan)
        │
        ▼
3. Logical Optimization
(Optimized Logical Plan)
        │
        ▼
4. Physical Planning
(Multiple Physical Plans)
        │
        ▼
5. Cost-Based Selection
(Best Physical Plan)
        │
        ▼
6. Execution (Spark Jobs)


1. Parsing (SQL → Unresolved Logical Plan)
Spark first checks syntax correctness
Converts your query into an internal structure called: 👉 Unresolved Logical Plan

2. Analysis (Using Catalog)
Spark uses the Catalog (metadata store - contains table names, columns, database info)
    It validates:
    Table exists or not
    Columns exist or not

3. Logical Optimization
Spark applies optimization rules to improve performance
    Common optimizations:
    Projection Pushdown → Select only required columns
    Filter Pushdown → Apply filters early
    Constant folding, predicate simplification

4. Physical Planning
Spark converts logical plan into multiple physical plans
    These are actual execution strategies like:
    Broadcast Join
    Sort Merge Join
    Shuffle Hash Join

5. Cost-Based Optimization (CBO)
Spark evaluates all physical plans
Chooses the best plan based on cost (data size, stats, etc.)

6. Execution
The selected physical plan is executed by Spark engine
Tasks are distributed across cluster nodes

If you run:
df.explain(True)  -- in databicks notebook
You can see all stages:
Parsed Logical Plan
Analyzed Logical Plan
Optimized Logical Plan
Physical Plan

